            <h2 class="section-title">üí° Current Market Assessment & Action Items</h2>
            <div class="info-box" style="background: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.1); border-color: #eab308;">
                <h3 style="color: #eab308;">üá∫üá∏ United States: Cautious - Flows Collapsing</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>Evidence:</strong> July 2025 inflows collapsed to $2.1B (from Dec '24 $87B). Foreign official outflows -$20.5B.<br>
                    <strong>Trade:</strong> Reduce position sizes. Very loose NFCI (-0.53) still supportive but flows weakening fast.<br>
                    <strong>Strategy:</strong> Defensive positioning until Aug-Oct data confirms flow direction. Use tighter stops.<br>
                    <strong>Risk:</strong> Medium-High. Flow reversal risk elevated. Government shutdown creating data fog.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box" style="background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1); border-color: #ef4444;">
                <h3 style="color: #ef4444;">üá®üá≥ China: Avoid - Multi-Year Outflows Continue</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>Evidence:</strong> 2022-2025 persistent outflows, no reversal in sight. Capital flight ongoing.<br>
                    <strong>Trade:</strong> Avoid BABA, JD, PDD, BIDU. Consider KWEB put spreads or short via inverse ETFs.<br>
                    <strong>Alternative:</strong> If bullish on Asia, play India (INDA) or ex-China EM (EMXC) instead.<br>
                    <strong>Wait for:</strong> 3+ months of sustained positive flows before considering longs.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box" style="background: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.1); border-color: #667eea;">
                <h3 style="color: #667eea;">üåè Emerging Markets (ex-China): Still Strong After $903B 2024</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>Evidence:</strong> 2024 finished with $903B inflows (+32% YoY). Momentum continuing into 2025.<br>
                    <strong>Trade:</strong> Long INDA (India pure play), EWZ (Brazil), VWO. Watch China weight in EEM.<br>
                    <strong>Duration:</strong> 4-8 week swings. These are longer timeframe trades than US.<br>
                    <strong>Best Plays:</strong> India (demographics + tech) and Brazil (commodity cycle + local reforms).
                </p>
